              <div class="change" id="trac-change-15-1369578652706573">
                
  <h3 class="change">
    <span class="threading">
      <span id="comment:15" class="cnum">
    <a href="#comment:15">comment:15</a>
  </span>
    </span>
        Changed <a class="timeline" href="/timeline?from=2013-05-26T09%3A30%3A52-05%3A00&amp;precision=second" title="See timeline at 05/26/13 09:30:52">3 years ago</a> by aaugustin
  </h3>
  <div class="trac-ticket-buttons">
  </div>
    <div class="comment searchable">
      <p>
A quick look at the code shows that DecimalField and FloatField probably suffer from the same issue. I'd like to fix it for all numeric fields.<br />
</p>
<p>
Since <a class="changeset" href="/changeset/4cccb85e" title="Fixed #19997 -- Added custom EMPTY_VALUES to form fields

Thanks Loic ...">[4cccb85e]</a> it's possible to customize <tt>empty_values</tt> per field. However, I'm not sure that feature was introduced for this use case. It appears to be targeted at custom fields (judging by the tests introduced in that commit). Maybe Claude could confirm.<br />
</p>
<p>
Besides, <tt>IntegerField</tt> already has <tt>empty_strings_allowed = False</tt>. Removing the empty string from <tt>empty_values</tt> appears to duplicate this information. So I really doubt it's the right fix.<br />
</p>
<p>
If we step back, the root cause it's Django's historical lack of model-level validation. Unfortunately I don't know the entire story. I'm just mentioning it in case it helps finding a patch consistent with the existing code.<br />
</p>

    </div>

